notesStmt.note: Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: A large fragment of the Pentateuch, punctuated and accentuated, with masorah magna and parva.
msContents.textLang: Hebrew; Jewish Babylonian Aramaic (ca. 200-1200 CE); Judeo-Arabic

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 2; ruled lines: 22; written lines: 22; The writing depends from the ruled line. Visible pricking. Ruling with hard-point is visible. Folio 103 is an addition, written in one column of 28 lines. Manuscript imperfect at the beginning and at the end. Masorah magna occupies one line in the upper and in the lower margin.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite square script with punctutation (folios 1r-102r); Yemenite square script executed with a different hand on folios 103r-103v.
